dataqual.logic: Permissable attribute values were checked using lookup values in ArcInfo Tables. Build was completed at publication time for Polygon coverages if necessary. Dangles were eliminated where necessary. All editing was done using ArcInfo 9.0 or ArcView 3.3

procstep.procdesc: Shape files were obtained from the the Counties and converted to coverage format. Resulting coverages were normalized and made structurally the same. Where overlaps between the counties data occured county boundaries were used to clip the original data and then the resulting clipped boundaries were unioned together to obtain one coverage with no overlap. Coverage was converted to the national FS standard and a source field was added to track the source of the polygon data.

Took Wallowa county shape file of WUI areas and reprojected to local projection system. Shape file had errors that required that shape file polygons be turned in to arcs only using xtools poly to arc command. Then shape file was turned into a coverage using shape arc. Coverage was then clipped to Wallowa county boundary. Coverage arcs were then appended to parent WUI coverage and polygon were then created by adding arcs and closing polygons. Unneeded pseudo nodes were removed and a build was completed on coverage. Attributes were then added in Arcview 3.3 and a dissolve was performed on all the attributes to eliminate redundent adjacent polygons.

Added the WUI boundaries for Baker County, supplied from Angie Johnson from ODF. Also did some small edits at her request to get rid of overlap between WUI boundaries. Specifically, I84 Corridor with Kamela, removed some small buffer segments from Wallowa County data that overlapped into Union and Umatilla County WUI's.

Added Grant County WUI Boundaries. Acquired a shapefile from Eric Scholl off the Malheur that was to the extent of the the State of Oregon. Used this coverage to clip out the boundaries for Grant County. Had to reproject the original shapefile before clipping. Then, appended these polys to wui_final. Final coverage, for the time being, wui_final2.

Aquired shape file from Gary Popek, forest service Heppner RD that had mapped boundries. He mapped the boundries from Morrow County. I clipped the Polygons with the Morrow County Boundry as the mapped polygons from Gary had mapped areas in Umatilla and Grant counties. These areas were already covered by the other counties CWP plans.
Reprojected to Region 6 Albers NAD83 projection

Added Wheeler County WUI areas and City of Walla Walla in Mill creek watershed area. The Mill Creek watershed overlapped sign. portion of Umatilla County WUI areas. The overlap area was combined into a combination area and attributed accordingly. There is two CWPP plans for the same piece of ground in that area.
Re-entered Grant County WUI's which seemed to have disappeared after a recent update.

Replaced Grant County Wui with a new feature class showing connecting 0.5 mile buffered roads, from a shapefile created by Eric Scholl and Laura Mayer. Converted to a geodatabase because converting the shapefile to a coverage resulted in extraneous polygons between the road buffers. Also deleted the polygons between the stream buffers in Wallowa County.

dataqual.complete: Coverage is only complete for the counties of Umatilla and Union Counties. More counties are to be added as they become available to the Forest Service. Umatilla County did not complete a CWPP plan for the whole county as the Western Half of the county was not included in the planning process.
